column10:
• The graphics are 2D and decent, good enough to enjoy with friends an amazing gameplay while you try to survive and endure your missions, you'll spend countless hours playing this amazing state of the art game;
• Very good for roleplaying even though i don't like it;
• Audio is reasonably good, some features of the game will even make you trip out xD; 
• This is a game that would be perfect for both teens and adults as it requires responsability, duty and a set of skills to make your missions very sucessfull. It's very easy to learn yet hard to master it, some missions will require harder grinding than others, danger is always looking out for you;
• You won't need much of a PC as this game won't demand anything or little bit of your computer, sooo potato PCs are welcome here; 
• It is very worthy of the price it has for its amazing content and gameplay.

In a scale from 0 to 10, I'd rate it a 9,8.

This game is amazing for anyone who likes multiplayer teamwork games, including a built in voice chat system.
Each round can become chaotic if your crew isn't organised so beware for that. honestly I don't have much to say, I just wanted to improve the game's rating by writing a review.
if you do decide to buy the game just know that it works best with groups of 3 or more. (though 4-8 is best imo)
